Haeundae Blue line park sky capsule!🚃 What is your favorite color?🎨 

📍 Haeundae Sky Capsule, Busan, South Korea🇰🇷 
📽 by @lullu_lily 
🎶 “AVIWKILA - I Like You So Much, You'll Know It”

📌 This slow and intimate ride offers access to Busan's stunning coastline, which you and your loved ones can enjoy. Situated 10 meters up in the air, the Haeundae Sky Capsule offers 80 sky capsules available in the colors yellow, blue, red, and green. Each capsule accommodates 2-4 people and travels at 5km/h on a 2-kilometer path, making it perfect for romantic dates or quality time with loved ones.

node.text:
Exploring underground jungle springs in Mexico!☘️ Who’d you like to experience this with?😍

📍Cenote Calavera, Mexico🇲🇽 
📸 by @thelosttwo 

📌 There are 6,000 Cenotés or underground sinkholes in Mexico, usually made of limestone and filled with fresh water. They are magical and the Mayans believed they were sacred! This one is called Cenoté Calavera, located just a 10 minute drive from Tulum. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Here are some of the others we would recommend:
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
1- Gran Cenote (Tulum)
2- Cenote Taak Bi Ha (Tulum)
3- Cenote Oxman (Yucatan)
4- Suytun Cenote (Yucatan)
5- Cenote Ik Kil (Yucatan - Chichen Itza)
6- Cenote Azul (Playa Del Carmen)
7- Cenote Dos Ojos (Tulum)

node.text:
Probably the most beautiful Waterfall in the world!💦 Have you ever been to #Canada ?😍

📍Niagara Falls, Ontario, Canada🇨🇦
📸 by @mthiessen 

📌 Niagara Falls, Ontario, is a Canadian city at the famous waterfalls of the same name, linked with the U.S. by the Rainbow Bridge. Its site on the Niagara River's western shore overlooks the Horseshoe Falls, the cascades' most expansive section. Elevators take visitors to a lower, wetter vantage point behind the falls. A cliffside park features a promenade alongside 520-ft.-high Skylon Tower with an observation deck.
